    <h1>LEI 101 - SSL and Cert Management</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <p>so in the LEI cluster we have two sets of micro-services. for th=
ose in the Control Plane all the external traffics are terminated by the lo=
ad balancer and the cert is automatically updated by the Foundry now, so we=
 are good with those. but for some Data plane micro-services we have had in=
 the Kubernetes cluster, such as Hiota-Ingress and Hiota-Engress, we will n=
eed to terminate the traffic at the Pods level hence we need to have a way =
to automatically update and restart the Pod when cert is due to be expired.=
 That is the background information that I like to share to you.</p>
<p>For checking cert expiration date, type the bellow command after updater=
 is finished.</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">[root@v=
m-cluster-cns09-1 ~]# kubectl get certificates -n hiota  -o yaml hiota-oaut=
h-helper
apiVersion: cert-manager.io/v1alpha3
kind: Certificate
metadata:
  annotations:
    ....
spec:
  commonName: hiota-oauth-helper
  ....
status:
  conditions:
  - lastTransitionTime: "2021-08-17T23:06:52Z"
    message: Certificate is up to date and has not expired
    reason: Ready
    status: "True"
    type: Ready
  notAfter: "2021-11-11T19:17:09Z"   &lt;---- HERE!!!</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence"># to ch=
eck cert for hiota-mqtt in the Gateway
$ kubectl get certificates -n hiota-gateway  -o yaml hiota-mqtt</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence"># check=
 the secret
$ kubectl get secret -n hiota hiota-asset-secrets -oyaml | kubectl neat</pr=
e>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>Where to find the cert, or manually remove them; and the sym link./etc/d=
ocker/certs.d, /etc/pki/tls/certs/registry.crt,</p>
<p>When a cert in GW was expired for somewhat reason, need to delete the ce=
rt and restart the Pod to get the new cert manually</p>
<p></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Inciden=
t of 2021-09-28 PM Demo cluster failed in dedup-speed data route
1.gateway VM (10.76.11.94) was out of space caused the deployment of dedupe=
 app failure. Cleaned hiota agent kvstore and storeforward db. Deployment s=
ucceeded afterward.=E2=80=A8
Because VM is not powerful and connection may not be good, to prevent store=
forward db stored too much data if connection to appliance got problem, it =
is better that not to pump data into the system when not using it.
=E2=80=A8
2. The MQTT on gateway server cert is expired and did not get renewed. A wo=
rkaround is to delete a secret, and restart the pod/container.=E2=80=A8
This issue may not affect the dedupe app since the app uses nonsecure ssl c=
onnection to MQTT. But we need to look into the issue.=E2=80=A8
=E2=80=A8
3. The dedupe app needs 2 routes, "Diesel Train Speed Sensor" and "Diesel T=
rain Speed Analytics Output". But only route "Diesel Train Train Speed Sens=
or" was deployed.=E2=80=A8
Deployed another "Diesel Train Speed Analytics Output" as well.=E2=80=A8
=E2=80=A84. Somehow the deployed dedupe app had problem in keeping the conn=
ection to MQTT. The connection kept disconnected and reconnected (don't kno=
w why). Thus dedupe app could not subscribe to the topic and publish the de=
duped data back. Deleted the deployed dedupe app, and re-deployed the app a=
gain, it started working.
</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">kubectl=
 delete secret -n hiota-gateway mqtt-secrets-ucp-p4ghgw1

kubectl delete pod -n hiota-gateway -l app=3Dhiota-mqtt</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<h4 id=3D"LEI101-SSLandCertManagement-GeneratingnewforKafkaafterLBre-config=
ured">Generating new for Kafka after LB re-configured</h4>
<p>&lt;issue reported by Silvia via lighthouse-acea Slack channel on Oct 11=
, 2021&gt;</p>
<p>LEI 4.1 changed the "hostnameOverride" value to use LB's name.<br>it is =
possible to regenerate a SSL cert with new SAN.</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">kubectl=
 get certs -n kafka kafka-cluster-headless.kafka.svc.cluster.local -oyaml</=
pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<h4 id=3D"LEI101-SSLandCertManagement-2021-10-14SlackchatfromHarunaHarunaKo=
chiyama9:00AM">2021-10-14 Slack chat from Haruna<br><a href=3D"https://app.=
slack.com/team/U021JU87T26" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow"><stron=
g>Haruna Kochiyama</strong></a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://hitachivantar=
a-eng.slack.com/archives/D029EGKSNCD/p1634227238043400" class=3D"external-l=
ink" rel=3D"nofollow">9:00 AM</a><br></h4>
<p>Hi Corey, FYI. Silvia shared her workaround about Kafka. Letting you kno=
w since it might benefit us in the future. Maybe its good to keep these kno=
wledge somewhere in the confluence for our future reference.<br></p><a href=
=3D"https://hitachivantara-eng.slack.com/archives/C01D7G5TY7L/p163413841504=
1200?thread_ts=3D1634042614.039500&amp;cid=3DC01D7G5TY7L" data-card-appeara=
nce=3D"block" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">https://hitachivanta=
ra-eng.slack.com/archives/C01D7G5TY7L/p1634138415041200?thread_ts=3D1634042=
614.039500&amp;cid=3DC01D7G5TY7L</a>
<p>Silvia Narcisi</p>
<p>I replicated the solution in the Acea-env (LEI 4.0) and finally, with th=
e partner Reply, we have found a solution to the problem which is a little =
different from what was explained in previous posts.Here some more detail, =
that could be useful for the <a href=3D"http://future.In" class=3D"external=
-link" rel=3D"nofollow">future.In</a> LEI 4.0 there isn't the&nbsp;<code>ho=
stnameOverride</code>&nbsp;properties in&nbsp;<code>kafkacluster</code>. We=
 added this property manually but the configuration has not been propagated=
 in the&nbsp;<code>advertised.listeners</code>&nbsp;of the&nbsp;<code>kafka=
's configmaps</code>.<br>To have the SSL cert correctly recognized from out=
side, we decided to add '*.c.aceaese007.internal' in the DNS name.<br>After=
 the re-generation of the cert (delete secret and pods as explained above) =
we were able to publish/read topic using trusted SSL.</p>
<p></p>
<h4 id=3D"LEI101-SSLandCertManagement-PPT-9726CustomerSupport-SSLCertDurati=
on-Kafka"><a href=3D"https://hv-eng.atlassian.net/browse/PPT-9726" class=3D=
"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">PPT-9726</a> Customer Support - SSL Cert D=
uration - Kafka</h4>
<p>After some investigation and testing. I believe the certificates for kaf=
ka can be updated using some manual steps currently. Kafka use both server =
certificates and client certificates. The server certificate mentioned abov=
e was created by operator kafkaCluster and the default duration for the cer=
tificate is 90 days.</p>
<p>In order to extend the duration of the certificate, we need to have a ne=
w certificate with the desired duration and the apply it to the pod. The st=
eps are list below:</p>
<p>Please note, the dnsname and ipaddress in the yaml files need to be upda=
ted based on the environment config.</p>
<ol>
<li><p>create an new certificate by apply the yaml attached ( cluster-certi=
ficate-1y.yaml )</p></li>
</ol>
<p class=3D"media-group"><img height=3D"250" style=3D"margin: 2px; border: =
1px solid #ddd; box-sizing: border-box; vertical-align: text-bottom;" src=
=3D"9d295ab30f216a3de91bfd20e4405abc" width=3D"250"></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>kubectl apply -f cluster-certificate-1y.yaml</p>
<ol>
<li><p>get the secret name which store the certificate data in kafka namesp=
ace. The secret name should be like: kafka-cluster-server-certificate&nbsp;=
</p></li>
</ol>
<p>kubectl -n kafka get secrets</p>
<ol>
<li><p>update the secret which store the certificate data in kafka namespac=
e. you can do that by deleting password, tls.crt, tls.key, tls.jks and repl=
ace them with the value in cluster-certificate-1y we just created.</p></li>
</ol>
<p>kubectl -n kafka edit secret kafka-cluster-server-certificate&nbsp;</p>
<ol>
<li><p>restart pod for kakfa-cluster and apply the new cert.</p></li>
</ol>
<p>For client certificates, we can also use the similar steps to get a new =
certs.</p>
<p>In the future, we may need to update the code so the duration is configu=
rable in the helm chart.</p>
<p></p>
    </div>
